<paragraph id="8BC7E024FFC35E2AFF788C88FC34FE14" blockId="5.[136,1451,1904,2075]" lastBlockId="6.[136,1452,158,473]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="263" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">
<emphasis id="B90C3C36FFC35E29FF788C88FE4EF862" bold="true" box="[189,450,1940,1966]" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">Nomenclatural notes:</emphasis>
—The protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="4C789BA7FFC35E29FD7E8C89FA8DF863" authority="(Cambessedes 1829: 260 - 261)" baseAuthorityName="Cambessedes" baseAuthorityPageNumber="260 - 261" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[699,1281,1940,1967]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Jussiaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="myrtifolia">
<emphasis id="B90C3C36FFC35E29FD7E8C89FC18F862" box="[699,916,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">Jussiaea myrtifolia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE99DD5FFC35E29FC628C88FB75F863" author="Cambessedes, J." box="[935,1273,1940,1967]" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" pagination="253 - 276" refId="ref3533" refString="Cambessedes, J. (1829) Onagrarieae. In: Saint-Hilaire, A. F. C. P., de Jussieu, A. &amp; Cambessedes, J. (eds.) Flora Brasiliae Meridionalis, vol. 2. A. Belin, Paris, 381 pp., plates 83 - 159. [pp. 253 - 276]" type="book chapter" year="1829">Cambessèdes 1829: 260–261</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
states that the species was collected “ 
<emphasis id="B90C3C36FFC35E29FE428CA5FAE4F81E" box="[391,1384,1976,2003]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">In sabulosis ad flumen Jiquitinhonha in parte provinciae Minas Geraës dictâ Minas Novas</emphasis>
”, that is, “in marsh along river Jequitinhonha in the part of the province of 
<collectingRegion id="49BC2EC6FFC35E29FCBE8CC0FB9CF83A" box="[891,1040,2012,2038]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
named Minas Novas”. No additional information regarding the type was provided in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE99DD5FFC35E29FD73831DFCCFF7D7" author="Hara, H." box="[694,835,2048,2075]" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" pagination="289 - 294" refId="ref4033" refString="Hara, H. (1953) Ludwigia versus Jussiaea. Journal of Japanese Botany 28: 289 - 294." type="journal article" year="1953">Hara (1953)</bibRefCitation>
, while 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE99DD5FFC35E29FC5E831CFAB0F7D7" author="Ramamoorthy, T. P. &amp; Zardini, E. M." box="[923,1340,2048,2075]" pageId="5" pageNumber="262" pagination="1 - 120" refId="ref4719" refString="Ramamoorthy, T. P. &amp; Zardini, E. M. (1987) The systematic and evolution of Ludwigia sect. Myrtocarpus sensu lato (Onagraceae). Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 19: 1 - 120. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 154203" type="journal article" year="1987">Ramamoorthy &amp; Zardini (1987: 62)</bibRefCitation>
, state the following: “Type: 
<collectingCountry id="F36FA0B4FFC05E2AFE9F8B82FE2EFF74" box="[346,418,158,184]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingRegion id="49BC2EC6FFC05E2AFE6B8B82FDC6FF74" box="[430,586,158,184]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
: Rio Jequitinhonha, 
<date id="FFC6C6E4FFC05E2AFCF18B83FC60FF74" box="[820,1004,158,185]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263" value="1817-05" valueMax="1817-06-31" valueMin="1817-05-00">May–June 1817</date>
, 
<emphasis id="B90C3C36FFC05E2AFC3C8B82FB77FF74" box="[1017,1275,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">Saint-Hilaire B1. 1532</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="54C35E86FFC05E2AFAC98B82FAFEFF74" box="[1292,1394,158,184]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">holotype</typeStatus>
, P)”. The “ 
<typeStatus id="54C35E86FFC05E2AFF0D8BDEFEA3FF10" box="[200,303,194,220]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">holotype</typeStatus>
” indication is an error to be automatically corrected to a lectotypification (Art. 9.10 of the Code), because 
<specimenCount id="9D7E2BADFFC05E2AFF2F8BFBFE1EFECC" box="[234,402,230,257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of the gathering 
<emphasis id="B90C3C36FFC05E2AFD9E8BFBFC53FECC" box="[603,991,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">A.F.C.P. de Saint-Hilaire B1-1532</emphasis>
are kept at P (barcodes P01819487 and P01819488). This typification must be narrowed to a single specimen by way of a subsequent lectotypification (Art. 9.17 of the Code). One of the 
<specimenCount id="9D7E2BADFFC05E2AFE218A33FD00FE84" box="[484,652,302,329]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
at P, 
<emphasis id="B90C3C36FFC05E2AFD0B8A33FD78FE84" box="[718,756,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">viz.</emphasis>
barcode P01819487, has a label on it left by Thennilapuram Parasuraman Ramamoorthy in 1978, annotated (presumably by him) “ 
<emphasis id="B90C3C36FFC05E2AFC728A4FFC74FEA0" box="[951,1016,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">TYPE</emphasis>
”. Nevertheless, this handwritten type indication is not effective, because the designation of a type is achieved only by effective publication (Art. 7.10 of the Code). All things considered, we designate here the specimen P barcode P01819487 as 
<typeStatus id="54C35E86FFC05E2AFB5C8A86FA8CFE78" box="[1177,1280,410,436]" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">lectotype</typeStatus>
of the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C789BA7FFC05E2AFA5D8A87FF7AFE14" baseAuthorityName="Cambessedes" baseAuthorityYear="1829" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Jussiaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="6" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="myrtifolia">
<emphasis id="B90C3C36FFC05E2AFA5D8A87FF7AFE14" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="263">J. myrtifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A further isolectotype is kept at MPU (barcode MPU011204).
</paragraph>
